The paper deals with energy efficiency in a multi-user multi-relay system with network coding, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of relay scheduling and power allocation also suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect. The optimization problem and algorithmic approach involve mathematical modeling and optimization (cs.MM) and discrete mathematics (cs.DC).
